comments: Tatum (BOS) briefly has his arm around Harris' (PHI) midsection and slides it off.
Simmons (PHI) briefly places his hand on Horford's (BOS) back and slides it off.
Irving (BOS) briefly engages and disengages with Harris (PHI) off ball without affecting his FOM.
Morris (BOS) makes marginal contact with Simmons' (PHI) front during rebounding.
[Observable in enhanced video] Morris (BOS) shuffles his feet.
Harris (PHI) engages with Morris (BOS) during rebounding, but does not affect his ability to retrieve the ball.
Tatum (BOS) makes marginal contact with his off-arm to Butler's (PHI) front that does not affect his ability to defend.
[Observable in enhanced video] Embiid (PHI) slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Horford (BOS) does not maintain legal guarding position and makes contact to Embiid's (PHI) body which affects his SQBR.
Harris (PHI) establishes himself in a wide screening position in Horford's (BOS) path, but contact is marginal and does not affect Horford's ability to defend.
Embiid (PHI) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Morris (BOS) makes contact with Simmons' (PHI) body which affects his driving shot attempt.
Horford (BOS) makes incidental body contact with Simmons (PHI) as the hand-off takes place.
Embiid (PHI) makes marginal body contact with Irving's (BOS) left side before blocking his driving shot attempt.
Harris (PHI) legally contest Morris' (BOS) jump shot attempt.
Irving (BOS) makes marginal contact with Embiid's (PHI) left arm that does not impede his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Irving (BOS) reaches in from behind and makes some contact with Butler's (PHI) body, but it is marginal.
Irving (BOS) makes some body contact with Butler (PHI), but it is marginal and does not affect hsi ability to retrieve the loose ball.
Butler (PHI) gathers the loose ball on his left foot and then legally jump stops prior to the start of his upward shooting motion.
Embiid (PHI) reflexively places his arms around Brown's (BOS) upper half as the screen is set and the contact is marginal.

LAR and LLS shows Simmons (PHI) holds Morris' (BOS) right arm and restricts his FOM as the inbound pass is made. The contact occurs after Tatum (BOS) makes the inbound pass and the play is correctly deemed a personal foul.
Embiid (PHI) legally contests Irving's (BOS) jump shot attempt.
RLS shows Tatum (BOS) makes some contact with his left hand to Ennis III's (PHI) backside during rebounding, but it is marginal.
